            .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240916-247-person2067">
                  WILLIAM 
                  BEST
               <interp inst="t18240916-247-person2067" type="surname" value="BEST"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240916-247-person2067" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240916-247-person2067" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I keep the George public-house, Queen Anne-street, Cavendish-square. I was informed that the prisoner had taken one of my pots; I went and found her about one hundred and fifty yards from my house, she was going backwards and forwards; I asked her what she had in her apron which was under her arm, she said only her shawl and a piece of baize; I felt round her and hear some pots chink; I delivered her to the constable, who searched her and took two pots from her, with the names of Freake and Pugh on them; she made great resistance.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240916-247-person2068">
                  CHARLES 
                  FREAKE
